The paper deals with the problem of range searching among curves, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves data structures and lower bounds, which are typical topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of semialgebraic range searching suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DB (Databases) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between space and query time, which is a topic in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
